# Files with MDX syntax that Mintlify cannot parse.
# See https://github.com/bazel-contrib/bazel-docs/issues/226

# Reference docs — docs2mdx.py output with remaining MDX issues
# "Could not parse expression with acorn" — bare {..} dict literals in prose
reference/be/functions.mdx
reference/command-line-reference.mdx
# "<https://...> autolinks" — not valid MDX (use [text](url) instead)
reference/be/protocol-buffer.mdx
# Raw <html devsite> wrapper, not converted to MDX
reference/flag-cheatsheet.mdx
# "Unexpected character `!` before name" — HTML comments <!-- --> not valid MDX
reference/glossary.mdx
# Devsite heading anchors {:#anchor} not valid MDX
reference/test-encyclopedia.mdx

# Starlark API docs — docs2mdx.py output with remaining MDX issues
# "Unexpected character `)` before attribute value" — malformed JSX in prose
rules/lib/globals/bzl.mdx
# "Unexpected character `=` before name" — malformed JSX in prose
rules/lib/globals/module.mdx
# "Unexpected character `!` before name" (mdx) / "Could not parse expression with acorn" (md)
rules/lib/repo/*
# "Could not parse expression with acorn" — bare {..} in prose
rules/lib/builtins/BuildSetting.mdx
# "Unexpected character `b` after self-closing slash"
rules/lib/builtins/CompilationContext.mdx
# "Unexpected character `)` before attribute value"
rules/lib/builtins/ctx.mdx
# "{@url ...}" Javadoc-style annotation not valid MDX
rules/lib/providers/DebugPackageInfo.mdx
# "Unexpected character `b` after self-closing slash"
rules/lib/toplevel/cc_common.mdx

# Query docs
# "{{ '<var>' }}" template patterns
query/language.mdx

